		       CROPPING IFF ILBM GRAPHICS
 Cropping is the process of cutting out unwanted portions of an IFF ILBM
graphic. The cut portions are limited to rectangular areas on the left,
top, right, or bottom of the graphic. A graphic already inserted in a
document can be cropped at any time.

 TO CROP AN IFF ILBM GRAPHIC: See fig 8-2
------------------------------------------------------------------------
 1. Choose the "Crop" tool from among the tool icons in the ruler at the
    top of your window.

 2. Click the mouse on the IFF ILBM graphic you want to crop.

