		       CANCELLING GRAPHIC ACTIONS
 You can cancel a size, move, or crop operation by pressing the right
button before releasing the left mouse button.


	  GRAPHICS COLOUR VS SCREEN COLOURS VS PRINTED COLOURS
 Final Copy tries to print in the colours in which they were defined.
However, when graphics are displayed on the screen they probably will not
be drawn in their true colours. When rendered  on the screen, a graphic`s
colours are changed to the colours that are currently available. If you
are using Final Copy Custom screen, for example, only four colours
(Black, White, Grey, and Blue/Grey) are available. So no mater what
colour you define for a graphic, that colour will be modified to one of
the colours used in the screen.

 If you are using Workbench 2.0 or higher, you can set the number of
colours used for the Workbench to more than 4 colours. For example, if
you set your Workbench to 8 colours, and open Final Copy on a Workbench
screen, 8 colours will be used to show graphics on screen. The downside
to this is that when you increase the number of colours for the Workbench
screen, the screen display may slow down.

 When the "Graphic Select" tool is selected, and you hold the mouse down
on a graphic (does not apply to IFF ILBM), the colours of the mouse
pointer will change to reflect the graphic`s colour.


