		    STARTING FINAL COPY FROM THE CLI
 Final Copy can be operated in either its own custom screen or on the
Workbench screen. The program's custom screen is a four colour screen
that uses predefined colours that you cannot change. If you want control
over screen colours you will need to operate Final Copy on your Workbench
screen.

 You can start Final Copy from either its Workbench icon, a Workbench
icon of a Final Copy document, or from the CLI. When you start Final Copy
fro m the CLI you can specify an optional command line parameter to
specify the type of screen you want to use. The options for this
parameter are:

 -WB  Workbench screen
 -CL  Custom interlace screen
 -CN Custom non-interlace screen

 In addition, when starting Final Copy from the CLI you can specify a
document to be opened. Below are example of starting Final Copy from the
CLI:

 FINALCOPY -CL WORK:DOCS/LETTER  Start FinalCopy on its own custom
				 interlace screen, and open the document
				 titled "Letter".

 FINALCOPY -WB		   Start FinalCopy on the Workbench screen.


